## 4. Current Architecture

- SQLite stores repository manifests and durable jobs with transactional claiming, leases, retries, and stale-job recovery.
- Qdrant stores one collection per repository. Embedded Qdrant is local single-process mode; external workers require a configured Qdrant server URL.
- LlamaIndex is used explicitly without global settings. Deterministic embeddings and extractive answers provide an offline demo/test path; Voyage/OpenAI are production provider options.
- GitHub credentials are request-only and must never be persisted. GitHub archives are downloaded before enqueueing; workers receive only local paths.
- Repository deletion is synchronous: mark deleting, remove vectors/files, verify absence, then delete the manifest.
- FastAPI owns API composition and an inline worker for local embedded-Qdrant mode. A standalone worker is allowed only with external Qdrant.

